Doc Del:<br><br>
I am guilty of bashing Class Lass pretty badly.  Something I'm not proud of.  She is a very special person and a causality of my irresponsible anger. I have searched for the words to wipe away my stupidity and she let me off the hook.<br>
I would now defend her at all costs with the same ferocity. She is a beautiful person inside and out and bears the scars of war.<br>
On occassions, I have seen muzzle flashes and tracers streaming up at me from a remote village or small house.  I reacted by placing rockets and automatic weapons fire on the &quot;target.&quot;  The post strikes would often revealed dead ducks, dogs, live stock, old people....and children..and VC.  I live with the pain of seeing the innocent laying among the antagonist!<br>
On other occassions, I exercised restraint only to fly to Hotel Three at maximum speed with a lifeless co-pilot whose chin rested on his bloddy chest or a crew member who hung silently in his harness!  For two years I felt that I was in a lose-lose situation... I guess I was.. maybe I still am!<br>
I will not tolerate the cheap shots of traitorious trash like Barry Spatz, but I will heed your advice on where to place the firepower of my convictions.<br>
I didn't come here to fight and quarrel.. I really don't give a shit why the war was fought.. I came here to visit with my Brothers who share my emotional wounds and seek that healing fellowship that comes from acceptance.  While here, I have gained many insights from the sober, sad, and often angry postings from those who discuss politics and history.  I watched Spatz strafe emotionally wounded vets with his insane pyschopathetic bullshit a long time before I engaged him!<br>
Thanks for the eye opener.. spray two cans of WD-40 on your ass and get well.<br><br>
MTF
